            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The enclosure has not been found but was probably a copy of CD’s Queries on expression (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7850.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 5 July [1871]</ref>; for the queries, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 19, Appendix VII). Hooker was about to travel to Morocco with <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3232.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">George Maw</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_261.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Ball</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7627.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. D. Hooker, 26 March 1871</ref> and nn. 11 and 12.</note>
